<subSubSection box="[199,1255,991,1018]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,152,1018]" box="[199,1255,991,1018]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,991,1017]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is the Latin adjective “ 
<taxonomicName box="[844,935,992,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Platylomalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflexus">
<emphasis box="[844,935,992,1017]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">inflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, meaning “bent inwards”.
</paragraph>
